Q2. What are the Key Features of React?
>Virtual DOM
>Reusable Component and Composition
>Javascript XML(JSX)
>Declarative Syntax
>Community and Ecosysytems
>React Hooks
>Component Based Architecture
______________________________________________________________________________________________________

Q3. What is DOM? What is the difference between HTML and DOM?
>DOM is Document Object Model,represents the entire webPage as a tree-like structure 
which allows JS to dynamically access and manipulate the content and structure of WebPage

>HTML is Standard MarkUp Language which allows user to create a static WebPage 
and defines the structure of the WebPage. 
HTML doesnt have a capability to interact with the User Actions 
and also it doesnt change once the it is loaded in the browser.
